post_text:
Plans and implements a program of instruction that adheres to the company’s philosophy, goals and objectives as outlined in the adopted courses of study.
Makes purposeful and appropriate lesson plans which provide for effective teaching strategies and maximizes time on task.
Presents subject matter to students to maximize learning opportunity and provides real-world, application based examples and learning opportunities.
Reviews student records in order to develop a foundation of understanding regarding each student’s abilities and needs. Maintain accurate and complete student records.
Strives to maximize the educational achievement of each student.
Utilizes a variety/range of student learning modalities in each lesson and uses differentiated instruction within those lessons.
Utilizes diagnostic assessment of student learning on a frequent basis.
Maintains accurate and completes student records.
Assesses student strengths and weaknesses on a frequent basis, provides appropriate activities to address student needs and generates progress reports as required.

post_text:
ICA Parents, please see the latest P-EBT update. If you have not applied, please don't wait! The deadline has been extended.

If your student attends Iberville Charter Academy, he/she does qualify for the benefits.

The amount of your salary is NOT needed to qualify. IF YOUR STUDENTS ATTENDS ICA, HE/SHE QUALIFIES.

If you currently receive EBT benefits, you will need to submit a separate application to receive the P-EBT benefits.

Please see the updated flyer with additional information. If you need assistance in applying, please email Ms. Brown (lbrown@ibervillecharter.org) or call (225) 255-2528.

post_text:
COVID-19 School Closure Update - Contact Information

Due to the COVID-19 National School Closure and Governor Edwards issuing a “Stay-At-Home” order, we are aware that some of our families are having trouble getting in touch with us.

To assist with contact during this time off-campus, we would like to provide you with the below contact personnel.

• Mrs Rivet, Receptionist
o (225) 320-1651
o The Reception Hub of ICA will continue to facilitate communication between our school and families; keep records of phone calls and student/parent contact information and schedule meetings.
• Mrs Paul, Counselor
o (225) 746-8485
o The Counseling Services of ICA focus on a holistic approach to students’ well-being. Areas covered are academics, personal, social/emotional and career that are in conjunction with the Louisiana School Counseling Model of the Louisiana Department of Education.

At this time, these are the basic people to reach out to. In the near future, we will include the numbers of other services/hotlines that we will have available to assist during this time of unrest.

Update: Packet Distribution Time Change

Parents,

The final opportunity to pick up packets will be Tomorrow, March 23, 2020 from 1:30 PM – 4:00 PM. We have had to change our previous times due to the Governor’s issuance of a stay-at-home order which will begin tomorrow at 5:00 PM

We will be hosting a Zoom call tomorrow to give you more information about our Online school which will be launching tomorrow. There are two different meeting times depending on your child’s last name. Please see the details below to join that call.

Our Principal John McCrary is inviting you to a Zoom meeting.

Topic: Hawk Talk!: Learning about Iberville Charter Academy’s Online Learning Space

Date: Monday, March 23, 2020

Time: 8:00 AM Parents of students with last names ending in A-M

9:00 AM Parents of students with last names ending in N-Z

Please check your email for link and information on how to join.

Develops lesson plans consistent with established guidelines. Establish effective rapport with students, staff members, and parents. Motivate students to develop skills, attitudes and knowledge to provide an effective educational foundation, in accordance with each student's ability. Work individually or in small groups with students to assess current level of performance.
Provide targeted instructional that meets the need of each individual student.

Write lesson plans and analyze data under the direction of the Intervention Coordinator.
Perform other duties as assigned by the Administration.

Student Management:
Assist with the supervision of students outside the classroom such as: field trips to assist with student supervision and safety, during play period, lunchroom activities, dismissal, etc.
*MAY PERFORM OTHER DUTIES ASSIGNED*

post_text:
